5. fugam] Glareanus went, and was at Basle, 23 April (l. 2 n.), on his way to Glarus (cf. Zw. E2. 34). By 21 June he was again in Paris (Zw. E2. 38).

7. fratri] See Zw. E2. 221, 252.

8. ibimus vna] Erasmus evidently expected that Glareanus would travel to Switzerland through Louvain. He afterwards attempted to secure Bani- sius (p. 124) as a travelling companion
